{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567396","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567396"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T00:00:57+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T00:00:57+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18969"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18969","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18969"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.03,0.02,0.06,0.01,0.89]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11703"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92809"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11703","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11703"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18969"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76168"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"18"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"4979"},{"type":"tags","id":"4986"},{"type":"tags","id":"4989"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5715"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11410"},{"type":"tags","id":"11412"},{"type":"tags","id":"11639"},{"type":"tags","id":"11645"},{"type":"tags","id":"11648"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27531"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27532"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31833"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92809","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/92809"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA parent brings their 18-year-old child with terminal cancer to discuss voluntary assisted dying. The child is experiencing intractable pain despite optimal palliative care. The parent requests voluntary assisted dying on behalf of the child.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most appropriate reason why voluntary assisted dying cannot be provided in this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Psychological assessment is incomplete","Terminal illness is not sufficiently advanced","Pain can be better managed with alternative treatments","Cooling-off period has not been observed","Request must come directly from the person seeking assistance"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe key issue is that the \u003Cstrong\u003Erequest must come directly from the person seeking assistance\u003C/strong\u003E. Voluntary assisted dying laws require that the person themselves must have decision-making capacity and make the request personally. Neither parents nor other substitute decision makers can request voluntary assisted dying on someone else\u0027s behalf.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ETerminal illness is not sufficiently advanced\u003C/strong\u003E - The scenario describes terminal cancer with intractable symptoms, which could potentially meet illness criteria\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPain can be better managed with alternative treatments\u003C/strong\u003E - The scenario specifically states that optimal palliative care has been tried\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPsychological assessment is incomplete\u003C/strong\u003E - While psychological assessment is important, this is not the primary reason for inability to proceed\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECooling-off period has not been observed\u003C/strong\u003E - While cooling-off periods are required, the fundamental issue is that the request must come from the person themselves\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEven though the patient is 18 years old and legally an adult, the voluntary assisted dying request must still come directly from them, not from their parent or any other person. The focus should be on ensuring the patient has capacity to make this decision and providing comprehensive information about all available options.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Voluntary assisted dying requires the person to have decision-making capacity and make the request themselves.","Substitute decision makers cannot request voluntary assisted dying on behalf of another person.","Voluntary assisted dying laws require the person to personally initiate and consent to the process."],"references":["QUT. End of Life Law in Australia - Voluntary Assisted Dying. [online]. 2024. [Cited 2025 Jan 21]. Available at: https://end-of-life.qut.edu.au/assisteddying","Medical Board of Australia. Good medical practice: a code of conduct for doctors in Australia [online]. 2020 [Cited 2025 Jan 21]. Available at: https://www.medicalboard.gov.au/codes-guidelines-policies/code-of-conduct.aspx"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76168"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18969"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"76168","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/76168"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-19T13:54:40+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-19T13:54:49+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11703"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"92809"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"18","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/18"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\uddd1\u200d\u2696\ufe0f","name":"Medicolegal","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type"